reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 23, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Nice idea but needs more work.
reviews.reviewText: I ordered the 10 pack which comes with two brushes in each of 5 boxes within a bigger box. Each inner box the brisiles are a different color. These were rated medium firm. I like FIRM! I know ya'll think that is bad cuz it could damage your gums. Heard it all before but FIRM gets the plaque off and if you brush daily there is no gingervitious. (I know, my spelling sucks) Never hurt my gums. I started with the yellow brushes and what i will call mushroomed the bristiles in a week, Went to black and these were better. Got about 15 days before mushrooming. So that's 4 brushes in 44 days. I'm gonna finish the other eight but am not holding out hope for the other eight lasting the next eight weeks. I like the idea of Bamboo handles just wish they were FIRM. So going back to REACH. I know plastic, ugh!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fabulous! Great price! FAST delivery!

reviews.reviewText: I bought a 10 pack of medium firmness bamboo a couple years ago and loved them. When I'd used them all and went to order more, they were no longer available on Amazon.I have been ordering/trying different brands for a few months now looking for medium bristly, but even though the description said medium, they were always soft or super-soft.I'd almost given up, but ordered these as a final attempt and they are exactly the right medium firmness I need. My teeth finally feel properly cleaned again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I try and be conscious where I can about the products I use in my home. These bamboo toothbrushes are a more eco friendly alternative to a standard plastic toothbrush. I buy them in a multipack and they’re on subscribe and save so I don’t need to remember to reorder them.I replace my toothbrush every two months and that’s about the time they start to feel less effective in terms of the strength of the bristles. So I would say they are of a decent quality as I find they last how long I would expect them to. This is brushing my teeth twice a day.
